| Typed failure taxonomy with per-type retry limits | Gem orchestrator classifies failures into `transient`, `fixable`, `needs_replan`, `escalate`, `flaky`, `test_bug`, `regression`, `new_failure`, `platform_specific`, `needs_approval`, each with retry limits/actions. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:273] [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:277] | Partial equivalent: spec-kit has halt conditions, confidence thresholds, escalation, deep-research failure modes, and tiered recovery, but not one universal typed task-failure table with per-type budgets. [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:21] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:28] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:299] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md:290] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md:101] | ADAPT | M | High: the explicit retry/action matrix is net-new as a cross-agent operational contract. |
