- [F-010-01] ADAPT pre-mortem: Gem’s required `pre_mortem` is more explicit than our analysis lenses and active-risk dashboard. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-planner.agent.md:199] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:142] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md:282]
- [F-010-02] ADAPT typed failure handling: Gem’s per-type retry matrix is net-new as a universal task contract; our equivalents are distributed across halt/escalation and deep-loop recovery. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:277] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md:101]
- [F-010-03] ADAPT auto-replanning: Gem’s `needs_replan → planner` is a useful typed route, but should map only to plan/spec workflows because our deep-research recovery already pivots via convergence machinery. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:281] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:81] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md:38]
- [F-010-04] REJECT flaky/platform-specific “complete/skip”: Gem’s leniency conflicts with our verification/halt model; adopt only the classification label, not the permissive completion action. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:283] [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:287] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:13] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:31]

### NEGATIVE / RULED-OUT
Reject adopting Gem’s `flaky` and `platform_specific` actions as-is: “mark complete” and “skip test, continue” undermine spec-kit’s completion verification and halt-on-test-failure rules. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:283] [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:287] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:25] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:31]

Do not replace deep-loop stuck recovery with Gem’s taxonomy wholesale: our deep-research machinery already classifies stalled progress and selects targeted recovery strategies. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:277] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/feature_catalog/03--convergence/012-stuck-detection.md:26] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-research/feature_catalog/03--convergence/012-stuck-detection.md:28]

### OPEN QUESTIONS
Should the adapted failure taxonomy live in `AGENTS.md` as a universal rule, or only in deep-loop/spec-planning workflows?

Should `test_bug` be added as a safe label that routes to “blocked pending test/fixture validation” rather than allowing automatic test edits?

